tourBios.curYrHigh: Earned PGA TOUR Latinoamérica status with a T3 finish at the Argentina Q-School, where he carded a 66 on the final round in January... Finished T16 at the season opening Avianca Colombia Open on his first career start on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica.
tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Made a hole-in-one to qualify to the HP Byron Nelson Championship, where he made his first career start on the PGA TOUR (MC).
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played college golf for Texas A&M University, where he earned several awards for his academic achievements... While attending St. Mary High School in Kentucky he won over 10 events, including the 2005 and 2006 Kentucky state high school championships, becoming the first player in 50 years to win back-to-back titles.
tourBios.personal: His father, Russ Cochran, played on the PGA TOUR and is currently a Champions Tour player… Favorite golf memory was traveling to see his dad's tournaments... His cousin, Rick Cochran III, plays on the Web.com Tour... Has two older brothers, Ryan and Reed, who are professional caddies working for his dad and his cousin... Also has a younger sister, Kelly... Was a standout basketball player in high school... The Chicago Cubs and the Dallas Stars are his favorite professional teams... Merion, Pebble Beach and Carnoustie are his favorite courses where he has been able to play... Would like to trade places for a day with any rock star: “It would be a pretty exhilarating experience on stage,” he says... Jack Nicklaus, Arnold Palmer and Lee Trevino would round out his dream foursome... Twitter name is @casecochran
tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt - Finished 2-11 at 2016 Q-School (exempt to midseason reshuffle)
